##Abrindo conjunto em fatorial: milho

::: {.cell hash='aula11_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-2_22bea13348a4c57429808b2ae618f014'}

```{.r .cell-code}
data <-read_excel("dados-diversos.xlsx", "fungicida_vaso")
data2 <- data|> 
  mutate(inc = dis_sp / n_sp * 100)

data2 |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = treat, y= inc))+
  geom_jitter()+
  facet_wrap(~dose)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](aula11_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-2-1.png){width=672}
:::
:::


##modelo de anova 2 fatores qualitativos 


::: {.cell hash='aula11_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-3_e0bcce3501990ed4a16b34683cb41203'}

```{.r .cell-code}
ml1 <- aov(log(inc+0.5) ~treat*dose,
           data = data2)
summary(ml1)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
            Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value  Pr(>F)   
treat        1 12.928  12.928  13.980 0.00179 **
dose         1  5.663   5.663   6.124 0.02491 * 
treat:dose   1  5.668   5.668   6.129 0.02486 * 
Residuals   16 14.796   0.925                   
---
Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
```
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
##libary perfomace premissas

library(performance)
check_normality(ml1)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
Warning: Non-normality of residuals detected (p = 0.050).
```
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
check_heteroscedasticity(ml1)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
OK: Error variance appears to be homoscedastic (p = 0.180).
```
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
library(DHARMa)
plot(simulateResiduals(ml1))
```

![](aula11_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-3-1.png){width=672}
:::

means_ml

## fatorial 3 fatores 


::: {.cell hash='aula11_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-4_8b3bf5a7bcdc288a89b097e2e9c9a378'}

```{.r .cell-code}
milho <- read_excel("dados-diversos.xlsx","armazena")

milho2 <- milho |>
  filter(tempo==8)

milho2 |> 
  ggplot(aes(factor(tipo), peso_mil,
             color = factor(umidade)))+
  geom_jitter(width = 0.1)+
  facet_wrap(~umidade)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](aula11_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-4-1.png){width=672}
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
## testar interção entre tipo de armazenamento e umidade

m2 <- aov(peso_mil ~ factor(tipo)*factor(umidade),
          data = milho2)
summary(m2)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
                             Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value   Pr(>F)    
factor(tipo)                  1  11215   11215  2375.8 3.64e-15 ***
factor(umidade)               2  42814   21407  4534.8  < 2e-16 ***
factor(tipo):factor(umidade)  2   2329    1165   246.7 1.79e-10 ***
Residuals                    12     57       5                     
---
Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
```
:::
:::



#Quando não possui significancia entre a interação, testar as variaveis independentes.


::: {.cell hash='aula11_cache/html/unnamed-chunk-5_6d827afc4b1ec8696071634d666c2fa6'}

```{.r .cell-code}
milho3 <- read_excel("dados-diversos.xlsx", 
                    "milho")

m4 <- aov(yield ~ hybrid,
          data = milho3)
summary(m4)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
            Df    Sum Sq  Mean Sq F value   Pr(>F)    
hybrid       5 105876446 21175289   8.688 1.02e-05 ***
Residuals   42 102371996  2437428                     
---
Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
```
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
check_heteroscedasticity(m4)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
OK: Error variance appears to be homoscedastic (p = 0.763).
```
:::

```{.r .cell-code}
plot(simulateResiduals(m4))
```
